caption: They staff is amazing and the food is delicious! They were recommended to us and we now have a new favorite place!
Best fish and chips in the city! Quaint little place with a fireplace in the back room.
Love the fish & chips! You won't find any better!

Best fish fry i have ever had, and the shepherds pie was outstanding as well. Great little place. Cant wait to come back when the garden is open. So glad they survived the pandemic restaurant closings!
Brilliant little pub. Good for a quiet beer.
The hospitality is excellent. The best time to eat in the pub is between 4pm and 6pm. Overall, I definitely reccommend Duke of Perth for people who enjoy Scottish food and beer.

I lived in the uk for a while and the fish and chips at duke of Perth take me right back there. You can still get them for carry out and it came with everything, the tarter sauce, ketchup, and even the malt vinegar and peas!!! Potato skins were great too. Please support these guys, they are a classic neighborhood pub that needs our help.

Absolutely a gem, the ambiance is authentic, the customers are lively and the staff feel like old friends. The shepherd's pie and mini macs were delicious, but the stovies are a must have. Recommended draft was perfect with my meal. We had a great time.
Great little bar with warm cozy atmosphere. Fantastic back patio in the summer, warm fireplace for the winter. The best Fish n Chips in the city.
I love this place. Wonderful ambience inside. It feels like an authentic Scottish pub. The outdoor patio as lovely as well. The food is very good and they have a great selection of beers.
Great hang
Amazing beer, scotch and food.
Great food and service. Loved it and would recommend it.

The fish and chips are as good as everyone says they are, get them!!  If you're visiting at night, don't let the dark bar confuse you into thinking they're closed. They actually have a huge patio in the back complete with cute lights strung across the whole area. On the menu were casual bites and classic English pub food, like fish and chips, haggis, and an assortment of sandwiches and sides. We got some beer, the fish and chips, and a chicken sandwich. The sandwich was good though not that special, but the fish and chips were absolutely delicious. Not too thickly-battered or greasy, and huge in portion as well.  This is a killer hangout spot for groups and would recommend that you check out their specials before coming. For example, on Wednesdays and Fridays they have all you can eat fish and chips!!
If you like to gouge yourself with fish and chips, then this is the place for you.  Everything else I've had is sub par.
Great patio area and crispy fried fish. AYCE on Wednesday and Fridays. Lovely list of beers of scotch as well.
Excellent fish and chips with peas. Flavor of Scotland
Beautiful bar and patio, excellent food.
My Wife and I visit this food truck whenever we are in town.  We usually split an order of fish and chips.  They have built up around the food truck to make a lovely area to sit and eat.
Best meal I had in Cali and the prices were super affordable especially considering the size of the portions.

I was so nervous about drinking/eating out because of Covid but had a WONDERFUL experience at Duke of Perth! They have a lovely garden out back, with a decent amount of spaced-out seating, and the servers wear masks the whole time. My partner loved his beer and haggis burger and I devoured my fish and chips! It was "all you can eat" but the portion was substantial and more than enough for me. I'm already looking forward to going back. Thanks for giving us such a comfortable and pleasant evening out.

I went to Duke of Perth last night for a 40th Bday Party and I was blown away. Amazing Service amazing Food and the White Lady Cocktail was just next Level 5 stars and I had a couple and they all have been testing the same amazing to have a great Cocktail thanks so much . This Bar is highly recommended
Wednesday and Fridays, they have all-you-can-eat fish and chips... AMAZING.   Not sure if they were better than the shepard's pie, because they are both fantastic.. highly recommend!
Great food and drinks!
I just left this location and had a great time. Daytime Mike is an awesome bartender. Very knowledgable about whisky and a great conversationalist. I can't wait to come back!

Wonderful experience. I’ve never seen these beers on tap in the US, and they’re served with just the right carbonation and temperature. The menu was pared back because of the COVID-19 situation, but what we had (haggis burger and fish and chips) was absolutely top-notch. Service was stellar, and the garden was delightful out back. Just go!
Liked to your place. Thank you!

(Translated by Google) A wonderful place, every centimeter evokes thoughts of England. Good-natured bartender, music buddy and good selection of drinks. I like it.  (Original) Замечательное место, каждый сантиметр навевает мысли о Англии. Добродушный бармен, приятеля музыка и хороший выбор напитков. Мне понравилось.
So good!!! All you can eat fish and chips!!

My girlfriend and I wandered upon this place on our first date! We continue to go back on our anniversary and are always met with a nice bar keeper. Looking forward to sitting at our table at the window and enjoying a terrific whisky selection.
Very good food and service.

I can only give 5 stars?  I would give it 10 if I could. What a fantastic place to have a nice dinner and a drink.  We ordered the bangers and mash and the Trawlermans pie. It was full of cod, salmon, shrimp,  scallops and potatoes.  Think a very light, very clean tasting clam chowder with a mashed potato crust.  The bangers were very flavorful as well and had a rutabaga mash as well as a traditional mashed potatoes with a brown gravy.  Both had peas too. Last but not least..... GET THE Llanfairpwllgwyngyllgogerychwyrndrobwllllantysiliogogogoch leek sticks. (Yes, that really is the name). They are essentially beer battered leeks that taste like the best onion rings there are.

Absolutely the best!! Came here for Friday fish fry and have to tell you that this is the absolute BEST fish and chips I have ever had!! Perfectly fried cod teamed with super tasty chips, accompanied by green peas to round out the entree. All you can eat offered on Wednesday and Friday. Refills were as good as the initial plate. Go here!! You will not be disappointed!!
Excellent selection of scotch!

Went here with my grandmother for the beginning of Lent. Unlike other battered fish that have more batter than fish, this fish had more fish than batter and boy oh boy it is fried to perfection. I tore off a piece to try it out and it CRACKED and that’s how I knew it was gonna be good. The fries are decent and the peas are peas I don’t know how you can go wrong with that but THE FISH. Oh the fish was perfect, I’ll definitely come here in the future my granny tells me I can’t eat meat on Fridays.

Fish and chips were fresh and well cooked. French fries were decent too and their dipping sauce (tartar sauce) was great. Waitress was friendly and attentive. Would recommend and even go again for the fish and chips.
Pretty good. Pretty expensive for pub food but the fried fish was great. The fries were ok. Good beer and they had a huge whisky selection too.
Genuine old pub ambiance with good food and beers
Great Liverpool bar!

Every wed & fri all u can eat battered fish served w green peas and fries. Don't forget to sample there fine selection of house brews and scotch.  Made even more Delicious when when enjoyed family and friends.

No TV and a live fiddle band, best restaurant +++++

What a find! Came in to escape the cold and had their Tuesday Prix Fix menu which is a great deal. Salad, fish and chips, sticky toffee pudding for $20 and I am so satisfied and full. Had the whole back room to ourselves and we cannot wait to come back!
Great atmosphere and amazing food. Be prepared to wait a while to be seated on all you can eat fish and chips nights. The house is packed!

Delightful and delicious! Daytime Mike is a King among men; he really understands what to recommend--their hot drinks are HYPNOTIC.

UNBELIEVABLE FOOD !!!! I have been to all parts of the country and world for that matter, I could not believe what we found in Chicago..I first stumbled on to "The Duke" in the summer on a bike trip going thought town, I got a quick bite for lunch and was fantastic, but only got a burger. and remember the portions were huge !, Then my spouse and a few friends went back for the Friday Fish fry and OMG OMG OMG , Literally the best and largest fish on the planet... I went and got the Bangers and Mash and this is my always order entree The feeling and atmosphere is as old Scotland as you will find, I have spoken with the owner and all the recipes are his Moms...and are well worth the trip, I am 72 miles away, we go 2 times a month. Ladies and Gents, Anyone looking for that old time feeling of a family cooked massive portion meal. Make time and bring a friend to THE DUKE !!

I ate here tonight with my family and it was a terrific experience! Super cozy bar/restaurant serving up hearty and delicious Scottish fare alongside a veritable galaxy of single malt scotches and imported beer. Not a TV in the place (and quite proud of that fact), so pull up a chair in front of the fire and watch the flames dance instead.  I personally recommend the fish and chips (which happen to be all you can eat on Wednesdays and Fridays). They are easily the best in the city, possibly in all of Chicagoland. The slow roasted meatloaf is a very close second.  For drinks, fans of lighter weight stouts like Guinness and Murphy's will really enjoy the Belhaven Black. If single malt scotch is more your taste, then you probably already have this place on your short list and if you don't, you really should
